      • calculateTotalCropLength

        protected double calculateTotalCropLength(IArrow arrow,
                                          boolean atSource)
        Calculates the total length the edge path is cropped.

        This method can be overridden to change the length that is cropped from an edge. The default implementation returns the sum of ExtraCropLength, arrow length and arrow crop length

        Parameters:
        arrow - The arrow at this edge end.
        atSource - True if the crop length should be calculated at the edge source. False otherwise.
        Returns:
        The total length the edge path is cropped.
        See Also:
        cropEdgePath(IEdge, boolean, IArrow, GeneralPath), cropEdgePathAtArrow(boolean, IArrow, GeneralPath)

      • cropEdgePath

        public final GeneralPath cropEdgePath(IEdge edge,
                                      boolean atSource,
                                      IArrow arrow,
                                      GeneralPath path)
        Crops the provided path at one end of an edge.

        If CroppingAtPortEnabled is True this implementation delegates to cropEdgePathAtPortGeometry(IEdge, boolean, IArrow, GeneralPath). Otherwise the edge path is cropped at the node geometry. If this would result in an empty path, the cropping is delegated to handleEmptyPath(IEdge, boolean, IArrow, GeneralPath) instead.

        Specified by:
        cropEdgePath in interface IEdgePathCropper
        Parameters:
        edge - The edge whose path is to be cropped.
        atSource - Whether to crop the source or target side of the path.
        arrow - The arrow that is used at the end of the edge.
        path - The path to crop.
        Returns:
        The cropped path. This is can be either the same instance of the given path or a newly created instance.

      • cropEdgePathAtArrow

        public final GeneralPath cropEdgePathAtArrow(boolean atSource,
                                             IArrow arrow,
                                             GeneralPath path)
        Crops an edge's path at the source or target side with respect to the given arrow.

        The path is cropped by the length calculateTotalCropLength(IArrow, boolean) returns for arrow and atSource.

        Parameters:
        atSource - if set to true the source side is cropped.
        arrow - The arrow to consider for the cropping.
        path - The edge's path to crop.
        Returns:
        The cropped path. This is can be either the same instance of the given path or a newly created instance.

      • getNodeGeometry

        protected IShapeGeometry getNodeGeometry(INode node)
        Returns the geometry that is used to crop the edge at the node outline.

        The default implementation queries the node style renderer for an implementation of IShapeGeometry. This method can be overridden to return an arbitrary geometry for a node.

        Parameters:
        node - The node the edge should be cropped at.
        Returns:
        The geometry of the node.

      • getPortGeometry

        protected IShapeGeometry getPortGeometry(IPort port)
        Returns the geometry that is used to crop the edge at the port outline if CroppingAtPortEnabled is set to true.

        The default implementation returns null. This method can be overridden to return an arbitrary geometry for a port.

        Parameters:
        port - The port the edge should be cropped at.
        Returns:
        The geometry of the port.
        See Also:
        isCroppingAtPortEnabled()

      • handleEmptyPath

        protected GeneralPath handleEmptyPath(IEdge edge,
                                      boolean atSource,
                                      IArrow arrow,
                                      GeneralPath path)
        Handles the edge path cropping if cropEdgePath(IEdge, boolean, IArrow, GeneralPath) would result in a cleared path.

        This method is called by cropEdgePath(IEdge, boolean, IArrow, GeneralPath) if CroppingAtPortEnabled is False and cropping the edge path at the node geometry would result in an empty path.

        The default implementation is to GeneralPath.clear() the edge path.

        Parameters:
        edge - The edge whose path is to be cropped.
        atSource - Whether to crop the source or target side of the path.
        arrow - The arrow that is used at the end of the edge.
        path - The path to crop.
        Returns:
        The cropped path. This is can be either the same instance of the given path or a newly created instance.

      • isCroppingAtPortEnabled

        public final boolean isCroppingAtPortEnabled()
